      {
         "id": "SECTION_prerequisites",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "<p><span id=\"htZoomImageMsg\"></span></p><p><span id=\"htAmericaAbyaYalaMsg\"></span> (<a href=\"#\" onclick=\"htCleanSources(); htFillReferenceSource('160fb48c-1711-491e-a1aa-e1257e7889af'); return false;\">Porto-Gonçalves, Carlos Walter, <htdate0>, pp. 39-43</a>).</p>",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "html",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "### Prerequisites\n\nIn addition to exploring the concepts studied in the previous texts of this chapter (<htcite0>), we suggest studying the text on the Bantu migration and the Shona culture (<htcite1>), speakers of the Bantu language, to understand the full context explained below.",
               "source": [
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "b5efc8f9-c268-430f-9681-7a43848ee48e",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "First Steps",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2024",
                        "month": "",
                        "day": ""
                     }
                  },
                  {
                     "type": 1,
                     "uuid": "8c10d904-305e-4a71-9ccf-28e6c83f7280",
                     "text": "History Tracers Team",
                     "page": "The Bantu people",
                     "date_time": {
                        "type": "gregory",
                        "year": "2025",
                        "month": "",
